---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-indonesia', text: 'Leaving Indonesian Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'destination-considerations', text: 'Destination Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best Asia Insurance', href: '/best/asia-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Gulf Region Insurance', href: '/best/gulf-region-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Malaysian Expat Insurance', href: '/best/malaysian-expat-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'asiaNetwork', header: 'Asia Network' },
  { key: 'gulfNetwork', header: 'Gulf Network' },
  { key: 'indonesiaCoverage', header: 'Indonesia Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', asiaNetwork: 'Strong', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', indonesiaCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$165/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', asiaNetwork: 'Excellent', gulfNetwork: 'Excellent', indonesiaCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$185/mo' },
  { provider: 'Pacific Cross Indonesia', asiaNetwork: 'Good', gulfNetwork: 'Limited', indonesiaCoverage: 'Included', price: '$130/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', asiaNetwork: 'Good', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', indonesiaCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$160/mo' },
  { provider: 'AXA Mandiri', asiaNetwork: 'Limited', gulfNetwork: 'Limited', indonesiaCoverage: 'Included', price: '$100/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Indonesian Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Indonesian expats. Find coverage for Malaysia, Singapore, Gulf countries, and other destinations."
  headline="Best Insurance for Indonesian Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Indonesian workers abroad form one of Asia's largest migrant populations. Here's how to stay protected in Malaysia, Singapore, the Gulf, and beyond."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/indonesian-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Indonesian expats are concentrated in Malaysia, Singapore, Saudi Arabia, UAE, Taiwan, and other countries. Healthcare access and costs vary significantly by destination. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Indonesian expats. Strong networks in Asia and Gulf, comprehensive coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks. Top-tier service quality.</li>
    <li><strong>Pacific Cross Indonesia:</strong> Indonesia-based with international coverage. Indonesian service, includes Indonesia.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good global coverage at competitive prices.</li>
    <li><strong>AXA Mandiri:</strong> Indonesian insurer with some international options. Familiar brand.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Gulf Worker Protection"
    description="Many Indonesian workers in the Gulf rely on employer-provided insurance. Quality varies significantly—some plans have major gaps. Understand your coverage and consider supplemental insurance for better protection."
    buttonText="Compare Options"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-indonesia">Leaving Indonesian Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Indonesia has the BPJS (Badan Penyelenggara Jaminan Sosial) national health insurance system. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>BPJS Kesehatan (Health)</h3>
  <p>
    BPJS Kesehatan provides mandatory health insurance for Indonesian residents. Coverage is tied to Indonesian residence and contributions. When you work abroad, this coverage doesn't extend internationally in any meaningful way.
  </p>

  <h3>Maintaining BPJS</h3>
  <p>
    You can maintain BPJS contributions while abroad to keep coverage for visits home. However, BPJS doesn't cover international healthcare—you need separate insurance for your destination country.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Indonesian Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Indonesian companies (AXA Mandiri, Prudential Indonesia, Allianz Indonesia) typically provides limited international coverage—usually emergency treatment only. Long-term stays abroad need dedicated international insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>BP2MI Registration</h3>
  <p>
    Indonesian migrant workers should register with BP2MI (formerly BNP2TKI). Some protection programs exist for registered workers, but comprehensive health insurance is still necessary.
  </p>

  <h2 id="destination-considerations">Destination Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    Indonesian expats face different situations depending on destination:
  </p>

  <h3>Malaysia</h3>
  <p>
    Large Indonesian worker population. Healthcare is accessible but quality varies. International insurance ensures access to good private hospitals. Language similarity makes healthcare easier to navigate.
  </p>

  <h3>Singapore</h3>
  <p>
    Excellent healthcare but expensive. Work permit holders have some coverage requirements. International insurance provides comprehensive protection and choice of facilities.
  </p>

  <h3>Gulf Countries (Saudi, UAE, Kuwait)</h3>
  <p>
    Large Indonesian workforce, especially domestic workers. Employer-provided insurance is mandatory but quality varies significantly. Supplemental insurance provides better protection and coverage continuity.
  </p>

  <h3>Taiwan</h3>
  <p>
    Significant Indonesian worker population. Taiwan's National Health Insurance covers legal workers. International insurance supplements this and covers gaps.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Domestic Worker Considerations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Indonesian domestic workers abroad often have limited employer-provided coverage. Understanding your rights and having backup coverage is important. Contact the Indonesian embassy in your destination for worker protection information.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage ideal for Indonesian expats. Strong networks in Asia (Malaysia, Singapore) and the Gulf. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 English service, direct billing at major hospitals. Indonesia coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Indonesian expats who want reliable coverage with strong regional networks.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent worldwide networks. Service quality is outstanding with comprehensive benefits including mental health and wellness.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium quality. Best for professionals who can afford top-tier coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Indonesian professionals who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>Pacific Cross Indonesia</h3>
  <p>
    Pacific Cross Indonesia offers international products for Indonesians abroad. Indonesian-language support available, familiar processes, Indonesia coverage included automatically.
  </p>

  <p>
    International networks are adequate, strongest in Asia-Pacific.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Indonesian expats who prefer Indonesian service and seamless home coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in the Gulf and Asia. Good value for comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Indonesian expats seeking good value with global coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>AXA Mandiri</h3>
  <p>
    AXA Mandiri is a major Indonesian insurer offering some international products. Familiar brand, Indonesia coverage included. International networks are more limited than global insurers.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Indonesian expats who prefer familiar Indonesian service and primarily need Indonesia coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="Get quotes from multiple providers to find the best balance of network strength and price for your destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance needs vary by destination. Here's what Indonesian expats should consider:
  </p>

  <h3>Malaysia</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Indonesian worker population abroad. Private healthcare is affordable compared to Singapore. International insurance ensures access to quality facilities. Bahasa similarities make navigation easier.
  </p>

  <h3>Saudi Arabia</h3>
  <p>
    Large Indonesian worker population. Employer insurance is mandatory but varies in quality. Many Indonesian domestic workers have limited coverage—supplemental insurance provides protection.
  </p>

  <h3>Singapore</h3>
  <p>
    Excellent healthcare but expensive. Work permit requirements include some coverage. International insurance provides comprehensive protection beyond basic requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Taiwan</h3>
  <p>
    National Health Insurance covers legal workers. International insurance supplements this and provides additional options.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Does BPJS cover me abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">No. BPJS Kesehatan only covers care in Indonesia. You need dedicated international health insurance for coverage while living abroad.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Gulf employer insurance enough?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Quality varies significantly. Some employer plans are basic with major gaps. Review your coverage carefully and consider supplemental insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Should I maintain BPJS while abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Maintaining BPJS keeps your Indonesia coverage active for visits home. It's separate from international coverage—you need both.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Indonesia visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Pacific Cross Indonesia and AXA Mandiri include Indonesia automatically. Other insurers offer Indonesia as a coverage region.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What protection do migrant workers have?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Register with BP2MI for government protection programs. However, comprehensive health insurance is still necessary for proper medical coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Pacific Cross or Cigna better?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Pacific Cross offers Indonesian familiarity and includes Indonesia. Cigna has stronger global networks. Choose based on destination and service preferences.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Indonesian expats need comprehensive international insurance—BPJS doesn't work abroad. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is our top recommendation for reliable coverage with strong Asian and Gulf networks.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium coverage for those who can afford the best. <strong>Pacific Cross Indonesia</strong> suits those who prefer Indonesian service. <strong>AXA Mandiri</strong> works for familiar Indonesian service.
  </p>

  <p>
    Don't rely solely on employer coverage in the Gulf—quality varies significantly. Understand your coverage and supplement if needed.
  </p>

</PageShell>
